  "time_ut": 1657191898,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0da0\u0dca\u0da0\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0dc4\u0dbd \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db1\u0ddc\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca \u0dbb\u0da7\u0da7\u0db8 \u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If the money is not given to the corporation, the country will run out of oil",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Central Bank Governor Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe said today (7) that if the oil purchase money is not given to the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation, the country will run out of oil.",
        "The governor said that the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation has requested 217 billion rupees from the treasury and since the treasury is unable to get such money, the money has to be given to the Central Bank of Sri Lanka.",
        "Governor Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe mentioned these facts at the press conference held today (7) at the Central Bank of Sri Lanka.",
        "The governor of the Central Bank, Dr. Nandal Weerasinghe, who spoke there, also said:",
        "\"So far the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation has requested 217 billion rupees from the treasury. They ask for this money in millions of dollars. This was not in the cash flow of the treasury. Then where will the treasury give 200 billion at once.",
        "Since there is no way to give it to the treasury, the treasury asks the central bank. Asking to mold money.",
        "For example, last week they asked for 18.5 billion for oil. The Finance Board decided to give that 18 billion. A ship that does not give it will lose money to pay. It becomes a more serious problem. 18.5 billion was given last week too because it cannot be denied.",
        "In 2020/21, the money has been minted to pay off foreign exchange debt. The central bank minted a lot of money for that. Money is minted to pay the government's foreign debt. The policy at that time was to pay the foreign debt. It was there until April. At that time, the government did not have rupees or dollars. There were no rupees to buy dollars.",
        "The central bank bought dollars with those rupees and gave it back to the central bank and paid off the foreign debt by taking our dollars.",
        "But with the current situation, we mold the money according to the need. We are not doing it with low interest rates like at that time. We gave 18 billion last week when requested. Now 217 billion have been requested again.",
        "It is necessary to decide whether to give it or not. If you give, we say that you give for this reason. If it is not given, it is said that it is not given for this reason. If that is not the case, the country may lose its oil.",
        "Inflation in the country may rise up to 70 percent in the near future. Central Bank implements monetary policy. We hope to control inflation by increasing the interest rate\u201d."
      ],
